A 25-year-old businessman who allegedly conspired with others to dupe one Eze Chris and 22 others of N10 million, on Monday, appeared before an Ikeja Chief Magistrate’s Court. The police arraigned the defendant on a four-count charge bordering on conspiracy, fraud and stealing. The defendant, whose address was not provided, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. The prosecutor, ASP Benson Emuerhi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence between August 2018 and March 2019 at No 21, Asset Con Plaza, Awolowo way, Ikeja, Lagos. Emuerhi said the defendant conspired together with others still at large to defraud the complainant and 22 others of the sum of N10 million by falsely claiming to trade in diamond. “The defendant, under false pretenses defrauded Chris and 22 others within Lagos through a company called wealthcom Investment Company and fraudulently obtained N10 million on the pretext of trading in diamond,” he said. Emuerhi said the defendant was apprehended following a complaint at the police in Ikeja. According to the prosecutor, the offence contravene Sections 287,322, 314 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Chief Magistrate Olufunke Sule-Amzat granted the defendant bail in the sum of N250,000 with two sureties in like sum. Sule-Amzat ordered that the sureties must show evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. The case was adjourned until June 6. (NAN)